															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204247" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456175281 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Feb 2016 21:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2461499">
									

<p>In this follow-up to <a href="/a-convincing-lyre">A Convincing Lyre</a>, Mobile Task Force Eta-11 (&quot;Savage Beasts&quot;) is dealing with a containment breach by <a href="/scp-339">SCP-339</a>. Agent &quot;Sandra Dee&quot; is pretty independent, but sometimes even the best soloists need a little accompaniment.</p>
<p>Thanks again to my team for the MTF Contest, the Site-19 String Quartet– <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457338983" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;">WrongJohnSilver</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cumaeansibyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(456737); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=456737&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457338983" alt="CumaeanSibyl" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=456737)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cumaeansibyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(456737); return false;">CumaeanSibyl</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=362048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457338983" alt="Smapti" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=362048)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;">Smapti</a></span>. Many thanks also to Hercules Rockefeller and MrWrong for review and feedback on the forums.</p>
<p>If you haven't found all of the MTF Eta-11 contest entries yet, below is a recommended reading order:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/a-convincing-lyre">A Convincing Lyre</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/an-impenitent-thief">An Impenitent Thief</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/project-proposal-2014-2112">Project Proposal 2014-2112: &quot;Dreams of Failure&quot;</a></strong></li>
