				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204247" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456220235 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Feb 2016 09:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2461785">
									

<p>I'm very pleased that you like this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the way Dee contains the skip using her suit was pretty clever</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As cliche as it sounds, this was as close as I've ever come to a character writing the story for me. When I started writing, I knew that I wanted things to go wrong, and to try to increase the tension towards the end, and to have *something* almost fall and make a sound, but I didn't know the exact details. I maintain that using the suit was Dee's idea.</p>
<p>And once that idea struck, a lot of other things fell into place:</p>
<ul>
<li>the fact that taking off the suit removes the last paratech advantage that Dee has, increasing her vulnerability</li>
<li>the fact that it could be something stuffed inside a pocket of the uniform that would fall - ie it's not a factor of a poorly designed suit</li>
<li>the idea that something stuffed inside the uniform could be something stolen, helping me refer back to theft and justify the title</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
